<div id="content" lang="en" dir="ltr">
Gondolin is having difficulties with Dragons. Turgon (located in the central courtyard) gives you the quest to get rid of them. The quest has danger level "25" but you might want to wait until level 30 before tackling it. <p>
The Dragon infested building is in the West side of Gondolin, North of the main entrance, shown by a yellow '&gt;'. Upon entering you find yourself in the top left corner of a smallish level, surrounded by hard stone ('mountain chain'), with some pillars of the same stuff in the room. 
</p>
<p>
Monsters: Dragons! There is a fairly equal distribution of 'baby', 'young' and 'mature' in the room, but beware, as the occasional ancient dragon has been known to appear. Some of them tend to converge on the player immediately, but others remain sleeping in the background. 
</p>
<p>
The best tactics here are to hide behind the pillars to avoid the breath attacks, then melee them, or to take them out using ranged attacks before they get to you, depending on character.  
</p>
<p>
You simply need to kill all the dragons to complete the quest, and a stairway appears in the bottom right corner. Go back to Turgon to register the completion, and the building becomes your house as a reward. 
</p>
